Summarize a cm Object

Source: R/cm.R
summary-cm-method.Rd

Summarizes some of the data in a cm object, presenting such information as the station name, sampling location, data ranges, etc.

Usage

# S4 method for class 'cm'
summary(object, ...)

Arguments

object

A cm object.

...

Further arguments passed to or from other methods.

See also

The documentation for the cm class explains the structure of cm objects, and also outlines the other functions dealing with them.

Other things related to cm data: [[,cm-method, [[<-,cm-method, applyMagneticDeclination,cm-method, as.cm(), cm, cm-class, plot,cm-method, read.cm(), rotateAboutZ(), subset,cm-method

Author

Dan Kelley

Examples

library(oce)
data(cm)
summary(cm)
